Prehistory: Age of the God-Kings

* Three great kingdoms rise up after three people blessed with unrivaled prowess in magic. These three use their unrivaled knowledge and power to create three mighty Kingdoms.  
* To the north in a large dark forest the Seelie/Edda live in cities enchanted in such a way that unless invited you would never be able to make your way through the dark forest to reach the carved oaken gates of their cities  
* Far southeast in the vast scorching heat of the opalescent desert there exists a bright and bountiful Kingdom. Lining the grand river that flows out into the mist covered seas that surround the continent  
* Far to the west on a mysterious continent the Third heir to the world fled here to avoid cities and the mass of populace deciding to live a free life inn untamed wilds where people brought low by the other kingdoms or people tired of living subservient lives in the petty fiefdoms that bowed their head to a King  
* There was a fourth kingdom not led by any mighty King but led itself a great coalition of Island city-states had formed a union hoping to be able to govern themselves with no self-serving God-king at the helm.![][image1]  
* Shitty visualisation of what the continent 2 of the God-Kings are located

The Fall of the 3 great Kingdoms

* After a long period spanning many generations of people the power of the God-Kings waned and their empires with them and after years of relative peace the Kingdoms turned on eachother each holding blame or conspiracy towards the other two believing them to be the reason for their waning power and collapsing empires.  
* The Woad-men of the west for the first time in hundreds of years sailed to the east and invaded the plains that lay between the Mysterious dark forest and the Opal Desert This event ignited an all out war between the Three God-Kings.  
* During the war the Three never noticed the Deserts getting hotter by the day, storms battering the coasts and a plague descended onto the inhabitants of the Dark forest  
* The three Great god-kings also were ignorant of their role they were playing as the power that sustains them was the very spark of life that churned through the planet dictating the cycles of the world as it urged them to destroy the other two  
* The three destroyed each other and themselves ending the war in a near mutual destruction of their kingdoms as each God-King held an irreplaceable spot in the function of their Kingdoms  
* All 3 of the kingdoms fractured and fell apart with time as the protection of the God-Kings left them each kingdom fell and fractured till nearly a hundred states were born in the years following the war.  
    
  TLDR: 3 God-Kings founding kingdoms find themselves stuck in the cycle of the world due to their “Godhood” and destroy themselves leading to a fracturing of the kingdoms.


  I envision the world has the world has ley lines or veins that contain the essence of life change and creation which is where the God-king's magic stemmed from as each was born as a part of this ley line and in the height of their Kingdoms taught the people how to harness this power from within them but also to seek it out in nature and harness it that way.


  The cycles of the world are dictated when the Life essence/mana/energy of the world in unbalanced having most of it exist in solid states outside of the leylines

  This happens due to the God-Kings' use of magic to support their kingdoms.


  I don't have names yet but I was thinking culturally just on this main continent you have a more germanic/Norse inspired culture that lives in the Dark Forest(Inspired by the black forest) and have them be the “Elves” of the world 


  The southern place would be Arabic/Egyptian in theme, maybe not really sold on that could also be a temperate place and have it be more in line with the Aztecs.


  But of course after the war and fall of the Kingdoms the cultures are diffused and adopted and adapted all across this continent.


  Religion

  I also have an idea where “Gods” exist in the current of life that flows through the ley-lines but they have little contact with people but more subtly influence events.


  These gods would be a combination of the ideals and categories humanity creates and past God-Kings who upon dying have some piece of them still exist in the ley-lines. 


  But over the years they get broken down into many gods split between many cultures.


  And their could exist a monotheistic religion that believes in a Gaia-like figure


  


  

  This is only my idea for like the “main continent” but I left in places like a Western landmass and the coalition of Human-led states on islands to leave room for more places.
